# gen198: F5 verification by RUNNING. parrot0 compiles+links a source file, then
# EXECUTES it and reports the program's REAL exit status from the process — the
# grounded "did it run, and what did it do?" oracle (CODE-MASTERY §4), not a
# guess. The exit code is read from the process, so a non-zero program reports its
# true code, not a constant.
> build and run tests/code/buildable/prog.c and tell me its exit code
< it ran and exited with code 0.
> run tests/code/buildable/exit7.c and tell me its exit code
< it ran and exited with code 7.